    Pyroscope
    public static class Pyroscope.LabelsWrapper
extends java.lang.Object
    LabelsWrapper accumulates dynamic labels and corelates them with async-profiler's contextId You are expected to call dump() periodically, io.pyroscope.javaagent.Profiler does that. If you don't use io.pyroscope.javaagent.Profiler, you need to call dump() yourself.

      • clear

        public static void clear()
        Emergency method to clear all ScopedContext references when memory leaks are detected.

        WARNING: This method should NOT be used in normal operation. It is provided as a last resort for situations where unclosed ScopedContext instances are causing memory leaks and cannot be fixed by proper closing in the application code.

        Calling this method will:

        • Remove all references to active and unclosed ScopedContext instances
        • Result in missing labels/labelsets in profiling data
        • Potentially create inconsistent profiling results

        Recommended usage pattern:

        • Fix your code to properly close all ScopedContext instances (preferred solution)
        • If that's not possible in the short term, call this method periodically (e.g., once every N minutes) as a temporary workaround

        Note: This does not affect ConstantContext instances, which are designed to live for the entire application lifetime.
